<title type="html"><![CDATA[Help with installing NES cooling fan]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2121&amp;p=17960#p17960"><![CDATA[
On my NES the 2A03 and PPU also get warm. The main inefficiency is the regulator itself, so you could avoid the issue by bypassing the whole mess and using a modern regulated power supply. There are also more modern regulators that dissipate less power. Finally, you might be able to use the glass case itself as a heat sink by thermally coupling the regulator with it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sun Sep 24, 2006 5:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
