I don't think changing the regulator would really change heat dissipation power, but for sure a single fan would consume a lot more power than the NES itself.<br />Overloading the regulator with a fan to cool it makes no sense to me. It is like a little cat that want to catch its own tail.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Sep 24, 2006 12:18 am</p><hr />
